<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-27T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-27T17:00:00-05:00" n="1354" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1354">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/898</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Jefferson</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-27T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 27, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your February 23, 3 p.m. Formation of commission by passage of law
                            satisfactory to Department. It considers that Minister of Finance,
                            Lindberg and Paxton to be third, will also be satisfactory. Commission
                            should immediately commence its labors and Paxton will leave for Managua
                            in near future.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>